7 o'clock in the morning, and the Holy Spirit came over me with so much love and so much grace.

23:28.602 --> 23:33.287
And it said to me, remember the promise you made to me that you would serve me.

23:35.469 --> 23:40.594
No matter what, I had to let go of my Judas moment.

23:41.410 --> 23:45.975
And I had to surrender to God all of what He had already given me.

23:49.439 --> 23:54.045
I don't want to do this, but here I am two years later saying yes to God.

24:02.114 --> 24:05.778
I got to ask, what are you holding on to?

24:10.978 --> 24:12.861
What do you need to surrender to God?

24:16.066 --> 24:16.546
That's tough.

24:19.210 --> 24:20.072
That's tough for us.

24:21.734 --> 24:22.976
Because here's the reality.

24:23.817 --> 24:26.001
We all have things in our lives that we hold on to.

24:26.742 --> 24:28.444
There are things that we have a deaf group on.

24:28.464 --> 24:31.128
There are things that, for whatever reason, we just don't want to give them up.

24:34.193 --> 24:40.242
We have said to God, Lord, I surrender all to you while knowing we're not going to give those things up.

24:40.770 --> 24:45.094
And like Judas, we talk a good game while we hide our true motives.

24:47.757 --> 24:49.859
And these two scriptures point that out very well.

24:49.939 --> 24:56.385
Luke 6 and 45 says, a good man brings good things out of the good stored up in his heart.

24:56.465 --> 25:05.194
And an evil man brings evil things out of the evil stored up in his heart for what the mouth speaks, for the mouth speaks what the heart is full of.

25:05.434 --> 25:09.618
I love the scripture off of us offers us two tensions.

25:10.722 --> 25:14.367
if you're a good person, or if you're an evil person.

25:15.168 --> 25:16.489
Guess who gets to decide?

25:18.352 --> 25:18.712
You do.

25:21.035 --> 25:21.836
You get to choose.

25:23.759 --> 25:26.122
Our scripture is not forcing us, it gives us an option.

25:27.103 --> 25:28.304
I choose to be a good person.

25:30.547 --> 25:36.335
Matthew 6 and 21 says, where your treasure is, there your heart will be also.

25:37.616 --> 25:38.898
I treasure traveling.

25:40.066 --> 25:44.371
I treasured my wife and I going to just do whatever we felt like doing.

25:45.292 --> 25:46.353
We put in our time.

25:46.713 --> 25:48.075
We raised all of our children.

25:48.495 --> 25:50.497
They're all grown and gone.

25:50.517 --> 25:53.801
This is our time to do what we want to do.

25:53.901 --> 25:54.862
I treasured that.

25:59.627 --> 26:01.529
But then God reminded me in my yes.

26:03.031 --> 26:07.535
He said, you can still do those things and serve me at the same time.

26:08.356 --> 26:09.938
So it's not like we're giving it up.

26:12.450 --> 26:13.111
She can do both.

26:15.314 --> 26:21.702
Remember Mary, treasure Jesus, but you just treasure money, but I want to remind us that Jesus, he treasures us.

26:23.485 --> 26:25.908
So here's another question for you.

26:25.928 --> 26:37.503
What is your worship revealing about the part of your heart that Jesus wants to heal, change, or claim?

26:39.146 --> 26:42.450
What is your worship revealing about the part of your heart

26:43.042 --> 26:47.229
that Jesus wants to heal, change, or claim.

26:50.273 --> 26:58.546
Not only does worship cost and worship reveal, but it also does this last thing, and I think this is my favorite point out of all three, it creates.

27:01.711 --> 27:11.026
When we examine Mary's worship in verse three, where it says in the house was filled with the fragrance of perfume, we realize that it doesn't end with fragrance.

27:12.386 --> 27:14.769
Because what is fragrant to do, it produces fruit.

27:14.849 --> 27:19.754
It creates something in the atmosphere, in the community, in the spiritual realm.

27:22.277 --> 27:23.879
Worship, listen to this.

27:23.939 --> 27:25.841
Worship is never passive.

27:26.782 --> 27:30.886
It always generates movement, always.

27:31.827 --> 27:38.595
See, passive worship is worship without engagement, the kind of worship where the body is present, but the heart is not.

27:40.257 --> 27:41.618
It's the opposite of Mary.

27:42.050 --> 27:54.745
in John 12, passive worship is Judas in the same room, hearing the same words, seeing the same Jesus, but unmoved, untouched and unchanged.

27:58.330 --> 28:02.675
Passive worship is participation without surrender.

28:04.497 --> 28:06.560
Listen to me, I wanna make sure that I'm clear.

28:08.462 --> 28:11.826
This message is not about condemnation, but it's about examination.

28:14.658 --> 28:16.802
I want us to examine the motives in our heart.

28:19.827 --> 28:24.896
Worship, passive worship shows up physically, but it stays closed internally.

28:25.577 --> 28:35.394
Passive worship sings the song, but it doesn't yield the heart.

28:35.414 --> 28:39.922
It attends the service, but never offers self.

28:43.170 --> 28:47.315
Passive worship says, I'm here, but I'm not going to give anything.

28:47.415 --> 28:54.204
I'm just going to check a box for this week.

28:54.224 --> 28:59.391
Passive worship is worship as a habit, not worship as a response.

29:00.512 --> 29:04.177
It's standing, clapping, listening, but the heart stays untouched.

29:06.580 --> 29:11.346
Passive worship is critique instead of devotion.

29:12.290 --> 29:13.952
Hopefully I didn't hurt anybody on that.

29:14.313 --> 29:18.318
I've been a part of a lot of churches that people just complain about the music being too loud.

29:19.660 --> 29:20.982
The coffee wasn't hot enough.

29:22.904 --> 29:26.068
We don't do that here though.

29:26.088 --> 29:26.849
So put that out there.

29:27.230 --> 29:28.031
We don't do that here.

29:34.840 --> 29:39.506
Extravagan worship creates a testimony that people just can't ignore.

29:41.378 --> 29:52.214
Striving and worship creates a testimony people can't ignore because it puts the work of Jesus on a display that is visible, undeniable and disruptive.

29:54.918 --> 29:56.781
John 9 and 12 points that out.

29:58.123 --> 30:07.917
This is Mary pouring out the devotion and Lazarus resurrected life became kind of a spiritual megaphone that echoes far beyond the walls of that house.

30:09.600 --> 30:11.122
What's your spiritual megaphone?

30:11.938 --> 30:12.759
How loud is it?

30:13.641 --> 30:14.462
Can people hear it?

30:16.546 --> 30:19.911
When your megaphone goes off, does it draw crowds?

30:21.314 --> 30:25.200
When your megaphone goes off, does it make people wonder?

30:26.142 --> 30:27.364
Does it draw people in?

30:33.113 --> 30:35.237
When your worship is real, please hear this.

30:37.300 --> 30:38.322
It becomes visible.

30:40.962 --> 30:44.386
When your worship is real, it becomes visible.

30:47.989 --> 30:50.252
Why does it become visible?

30:51.333 --> 30:52.674
Because your life has changed.

30:54.776 --> 30:59.862
People see your transformed life because your worship is visible.

31:03.365 --> 31:07.890
When worship is visible, you give when it's uncomfortable without expectation.

31:10.466 --> 31:10.806
Why?

31:10.887 --> 31:12.068
Because God is worthy.

31:16.333 --> 31:17.695
Your worship becomes visible.

31:18.977 --> 31:26.746
You walk around with this unexpected joy, this unexplainable peace when your worship is visible.

31:30.010 --> 31:32.573
Your worship creates a curiosity in others.

31:33.575 --> 31:34.276
Did you know that?

31:37.379 --> 31:39.442
When I'm up here jumping around on stage,

31:39.906 --> 31:41.208
Acting like a crazy man.

31:41.268 --> 31:43.993
You can admit it.

31:44.014 --> 31:44.595
Yes, I do.

31:46.498 --> 31:50.846
My hope is that you guys are wondering why I worship the way that I worship.

31:52.008 --> 31:54.352
And I'll tell you because God is real to me.

31:55.535 --> 31:56.957
God is worthy to me.

31:58.440 --> 32:01.746
And I have a testimony to share with you as to why.

32:10.722 --> 32:15.949
Your worship creates a confrontation with darkness.

32:18.812 --> 32:18.993
It does.

32:22.477 --> 32:26.182
The chief priest wanted to kill Lazarus because he was too loud.

32:27.844 --> 32:34.252
Worship always threatens the powers that prefer silence, control, and spiritual apathy.

32:35.173 --> 32:39.058
When we confront darkness, we do what Chad told us last week

32:39.330 --> 32:45.800
And we say these few words, not on my watch.

32:52.110 --> 32:59.281
Your worship, your worship creates a movement toward Jesus.

33:05.371 --> 33:07.634
The Bible says many believe because of Lazarus.

33:08.962 --> 33:10.664
Many believe because of him.

33:15.229 --> 33:16.610
His life became a bridge.

33:18.452 --> 33:19.734
Your life is a bridge.

33:22.877 --> 33:25.920
Mary's life became a catalyst.

33:25.940 --> 33:27.362
Your life is a catalyst.

33:31.506 --> 33:33.949
Worship doesn't just end in the worship center.

33:34.990 --> 33:36.572
It doesn't just end in this room.

33:37.392 --> 33:38.834
Your worship is carried

33:39.618 --> 33:46.574
from the doors to the parking lot, to Dunlap, to Chilla Coffee, to East Peoria.

33:46.594 --> 33:51.826
Your worship is carried to the East Bluff where we are planting a new church.

34:09.250 --> 34:17.883
If you're having a worship cost, you guys, it reveals and it creates all three of those.

34:21.728 --> 34:22.990
So this week, do me a favor.

34:25.694 --> 34:28.238
Don't just remember what Jesus brought you out of, show it.

34:29.259 --> 34:36.850
Let your choices, your conversations and your generosity say he is worth

34:40.322 --> 34:44.968
Find one way this week to sow Jesus, and He matters to you.

34:46.470 --> 34:55.743
One choice, one moment, one act of love, your worship, your extravagant worship.

34:58.687 --> 35:06.838
We're gonna pray, and after that, we're gonna sing another song where you join us with your extravagant worship.

35:08.180 --> 35:09.522
Heavenly Father, we thank you.

35:12.034 --> 35:13.055
Thank you for your word.

35:15.118 --> 35:19.164
Father, we ask that it would go out and not return void.

35:21.828 --> 35:27.496
We ask Father that we would find ourselves in that word and we would be forever changed.

35:28.938 --> 35:33.585
And when we left this place, we would be different.

35:35.288 --> 35:39.794
Now Father, as we sing songs of worship, songs of Zion to your name,

35:41.730 --> 35:45.456
praying hope that our worship is pleasing in your sight.

35:46.017 --> 35:50.384
And we lift every voice and we sing to the God of glory.

35:51.546 --> 35:51.827
Why?

35:51.907 --> 35:56.975
Because you are worthy in Jesus name.

35:56.995 --> 35:57.296
Amen.

35:57.717 --> 35:58.578
Come on, let's stand.

